quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  29,31,"And when Our messengers came to Abraham{1}with the glad tidings, they said, “We are going to destroy the people of this town; indeed, its people have been unjust.”",1:[Qira’at: Though pronounced in Arabic as <i>Ibrahim</i>, Hisham and Ibn Zekwan in one of his narrations read it as: “Abraham”.]
  29,32,"He said, “Yet Lot is in it.” They said, “We know better of who is in it; we will most surelydeliver{1}himand his family, except for his wife; she has become one of those who linger behind.”",1:[Qira’at: Hamza, Al-Kesa’i, Ya’qub and Khalaf read it as: “…we will most surely save him…”]
  29,33,"Then, when Our messengers came to Lot, he was troubled and distressed on their account. But they said, “Do not fear nor grieve; we will deliver{1}youand your family, except for your wife; she has become one of those who linger behind.",1:[Qira’at: All except for Nafie’, Abu Amr, Ibn Amer, Hafs and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…we will save you and…”]
  29,34,"Indeed, We will send{1}downupon the people of this town a torment from heaven on account of having been defiantly disobedient.”",1:[Qira’at: Ibn Amer read it as: “Indeed, We will send from on high upon the people of this town…”]
  29,35,"And We left behind something of it as an evident sign for people who reason."
  29,36,"And to Midian<i>(We sent) </i>their brother Shuʻaib. So he said, “O my people, worship Allah and expect the Last Day, and do not go wickedly about the land, corrupting it.”"
  29,37,"But they disbelieved him, so the Tremor overtook them and they became lifeless bodies in their home."
  29,38,"And ʻĀd{1}and Thamûd{2}as well, as it has become evident for you<sup>pl </sup>from their<i>(ruined) </i>residences. And Satan adorned their deeds for them, barring them from the way, even though they could see.",1:[The pagan tribe of Prophet Hûd.],2:[The pagan tribe of Prophet Salih.]
